reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Air Wick Stick Ups Air Freshener - Sparkling Citrus Bliss
reviews.reviewText: I recently tried the Air Wick Stick Ups Air Freshener in the Sparkling Citrus scent, and I must say, it brought a refreshing and delightful aroma to my living space. These convenient little air fresheners are a practical and discreet way to keep the surroundings smelling fresh without overpowering the senses.Installing the Stick Ups air fresheners couldn't be simpler. The adhesive backing allows you to stick them virtually anywhere, and they stay in place securely. I placed them in various locations, including my bathroom, closet, and even inside the car, and they worked like a charm.Given their compact size, I was pleasantly surprised by their longevity. Each Stick Up air freshener lasted for several weeks, effectively maintaining a pleasant scent throughout the designated area.These air fresheners are small and discreet, making them inconspicuous in any setting. They blend in well with the surroundings, and visitors often complimented the fresh fragrance without even realizing the source. The Stick Ups are not restricted to just one location. You can use them in various areas of your home or office, providing flexibility in enhancing the ambiance wherever needed. the Air Wick Stick Ups Air Freshener in Sparkling Citrus is a practical and effective solution to keep your living spaces smelling fresh and inviting. Its invigorating scent, easy application, and long-lasting performance make it a reliable option for maintaining a pleasant ambiance. Whether you need to freshen up a small room, a closet, or your car, these Stick Ups are a great choice. Although more scent options would be appreciated, the Sparkling Citrus fragrance alone is enough to uplift the mood and create a welcoming atmosphere. I highly recommend giving these air fresheners a try for a delightful and hassle-free scenting experience.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are great for our "recycling closet"
reviews.reviewText: We had to have something WITHOUT a plug and had a hard time finding them in our local stores. We were so excited to find them on Amazon. We keep our recycling in a kitchen closet. Although we washout the containers before we put them in the bins, sometimes there is something left behind that smells. These stick ups are great for helping mask the odor until we take the recycling each week.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Hides poop smell
reviews.reviewText: We used this in our covered trash for kitty poo. Poo goes in a poo bag, then in scented trash bag and closed. Still smelled up the whole garage. This finally got rid of the smell. 4/5 stars because it didn't stick to inside of trash can lid (and didn't seem to be making any difference INSIDE the trash). We ended up sticking it on the top and then couldn't smell kitty poo anymore. Do be aware - it is extremely fragrant and strongly citrusy smelling which may bother some people I like it. And definitely prefer over poo. :-)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not sticky enough
reviews.reviewText: Used in our large garbage can. Scent was okay -- not quite strong enough for that size can I guess. But unfortunately, it would never stay "stuck" to the lid, even though it was new and cleaned. Ended up using duct tape to hold it in place. Won't buy again for this purpose.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not Worth the Money
reviews.reviewText: I thought I would be able to use these on the lid of my trashcan as pictured on the product packaging. It fell off into the trashcan so would not recommend it for use on a trashcan lid. The item fell off into the trash after ensuring the lid was clean before applying and it was not full. The smell was an odd citrus smell. I cannot rate the product on how long it would last because I accidentally threw it away after just a couple of weeks on the trashcan lid. The product is also fairly large in size. I thought they would be a bit smaller. They are the size of your palm roughly. They are also not slim, about 3/4 to 1 inch thick.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality and Function
reviews.reviewText: I am completely satisfied with the item. It does just what is described on the Amazon site. The quality and workmanship is excellent. It has a slight odor but that's OK since it seems to work in reducing the food odors in the sealed kitchen garbage can. You only smell it if you stick your nose into the can.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for inside garbage cans!
reviews.reviewText: It's a BATTLE to keep my plastic kitchen garbage can from stinking. I keep it clean, don't let food or trash build up, but yeah, it's funky. One of these stuck inside the top lid and another on the bottom below the trash bag helps a lot. And they're cheap and easy to use. Definitely a decent solution!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Smells good but not strong enough
reviews.reviewText: I love the idea, smells good but I used both in my small sliding door closet and I can’t really smell it.. I think I’d have to put 4 in order to actually get a scent. I looked inside and they have very little of the gel that makes it smell. I think if they’d fill it up a bit more this would be a better product. However, because of the price I really can’t complain too much!
Did not stick properly got the dustbin . Fragrance is ok
Easy to use. Nice mild scent.

reviews.reviewTitle: Works pretty good outside our litter room
reviews.reviewText: Lasts a good amount of time and you can replace the top part with the scent puck without taking the whole thing off the wall, so that is nice.
